f=Executive Office/marcus/operational/commands/marcus-commands.md · p=single routing reference marcus: which natural-language phrase shortcut invokes which skill. Saves marcus having scan five skill files figure out what request asking for. trigger phrases below pulled directly skill's "When Use" section file indexes them, doesn't redefine them. · h2:Trigger Table=\| Skill \| Natural-language triggers \| Shortcut \| · h2:Trigger Table=\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Trigger Table=\| decision-critic \| "big decision," "stress test this," "is this plan solid," "pressure-test this strategy," "before I commit to X" \| `/marcus-decide` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| okr-cascade \| "set OKRs," "quarterly planning," "cascade objectives," "what should [team]'s goals be this quarter" \| `/marcus-okr` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| venture-priority-matrix \| "which venture first," "prioritize initiatives," "resource conflict," "who gets the budget" \| `/marcus-rank` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| strategy-advisor \| "evaluate strategic options," "high-impact business decision," "competitive analysis," "set organizational direction," "assess market opportunity," "plan long-term initiative" \| `/marcus-strategy` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| vision-exploration \| "what could this become," "explore the end-state," "where could this go long-term," "far-out possibilities for X" \| `/marcus-vision` \| · h2:Shortcut Usage=Shortcuts quick-reference convenience, replacement natural-language triggers either form route skill. request matches one row (e.g. it's big decision mentions OKRs), route skill matching *primary* ask, note related skill relevant follow-up rather running once. · f=request doesn't clearly match any row, don't force nearest skill ask clarifying question first, consistent `okr-cascade`'s Phase `decision-critic`'s Phase guidance stop ask rather guess.